'''卡胡拉威島'''（{{lang-haw|Kahoʻolawe}}{{IPA-haw|kəˈhoʔoˈlɐve|}}，{{lang-en|Kahoolawe}}{{IPAc-en|k|ɑː|ˌ|h|oʊ|oʊ|ˈ|l|ɑː|w|eɪ|,_|-|v|eɪ}}<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dictionary.com/browse/kahoolawe |title=Dictionary.com |access-date=2020-04-29 |archive-date=2020-08-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200815102139/https://www.dictionary.com/browse/kahoolawe |dead-url=no }}</ref>）是[[夏威夷群島|夏威夷群島]]中八個主要[[火山島|火山島]]中最小的一個。位於[[茂宜島|茂宜島]]西南約{{convert|11|km|mi|0}}。島嶼長{{convert|18|km|mi}}，寬{{convert|9.7|km|mi}}，土地面積{{convert|116.47|km2|sqmi|2}}<ref name="SizeRef">{{cite web | url=http://www.hawaii.gov/dbedt/info/economic/databook/db2004/section05.pdf | title=Table 5.08 - Land Area of Islands: 2000 | work=2004 State of Hawaii Data Book | publisher=State of Hawaii | year=2004 | accessdate=2007-07-23 | format=PDF | archive-date=2012-02-01 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120201054628/http://hawaii.gov/dbedt/info/economic/databook/db2004/section05.pdf | dead-url=yes }}</ref>。全島的最高點是Pua Moaulanui山頂的Lua Makika火山口，海拔約{{convert|450|m|ft}}<ref name="ElevationRef">{{cite web | url=http://www.hawaii.gov/dbedt/info/economic/databook/db2004/section05.pdf | title=Table 5.11 - Elevations of Major Summits | work=2004 State of Hawaii Data Book | publisher=State of Hawaii | year=2004 | accessdate=2007-07-23 | format=PDF | archive-date=2012-02-01 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120201054628/http://hawaii.gov/dbedt/info/economic/databook/db2004/section05.pdf | dead-url=yes }}</ref>。卡胡拉威島相對乾燥，年平均降雨量少於{{convert|650|mm|in}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.state.hi.us/dlnr/dofaw/cwcs/files/NAAT%20final%20CWCS/Chapters/CHAPTER%206%20kahoolawe%20NAAT%20final%20!.pdf |title=Kahoolawe |work=Hawaii's Comprehensive Wildlife Conservation Strategy |publisher=Hawaii Division of Land and Natural Resources |access-date=2020-04-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120308030328/http://www.state.hi.us/dlnr/dofaw/cwcs/files/NAAT%20final%20CWCS/Chapters/CHAPTER%206%20kahoolawe%20NAAT%20final%20!.pdf |archive-date=2012-03-08 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>，原因是東北方[[茂宜島|茂宜島]]上海拔{{convert|3055|m|ft}}的[[哈萊亞卡拉火山|哈萊亞卡拉火山]]擋住了濕潤的東北風，使低海拔的卡胡拉威島無法產生大量的[[降水|地形降水]]。島上超過四分之一的土壤是受[[侵蝕作用|侵蝕]]的硬質腐泥土，大部分位於山頂附近的裸露表面。

由於缺乏[[淡水|淡水]]，卡胡拉威島一直人口稀少<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://evols.library.manoa.hawaii.edu/bitstream/handle/10524/616/JL18045.pdf?sequence=1 |title=Robert C. Schmitt and Carol L. Silva: Population Trends on Kahoolawe |access-date=2020-04-29 |archive-date=2020-08-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200815102150/https://evols.library.manoa.hawaii.edu/bitstream/handle/10524/616/JL18045.pdf?sequence=1 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。[[第二次世界大戰|第二次世界大戰]]期間，這裡被[[美軍|美軍]]用作訓練轟炸的靶場。經過數十年的抗議，[[美國海軍|美國海軍]]在1990年結束了在卡胡拉威島的實彈訓練，並於1994年將整個島嶼移交給[[夏威夷州|夏威夷州]]管轄。[[夏威夷州議會|夏威夷州議會]]決議在此建立卡胡拉威島保護區（Kahoʻolawe Island Reserve），以恢復和監督這座島嶼及其周圍水域。如今，卡胡拉威島只能用於發展[[夏威夷族|夏威夷原住民]]的文化、精神和生計。島上現仍有大量當年作為靶場使用時殘留的未爆彈。

卡胡拉威島上沒有永久居民<ref>[https://www.census.gov|b=50|l=en|t=4001|zf=0.0|ms=sel_00dec|dw=0.3235256323641746|dh=0.22787245954044197|dt=gov.census.aff.domain.map.EnglishMapExtent|if=gif|cx=-156.5954874499071|cy=20.568734378783724|zl=5|pz=5|bo=318:317:316:314:313:323:319|bl=362:393:358:357:356:355:354|ft=350:349:335:389:388:332:331|fl=381:403:204:380:369:379:368|g=14000US15009031600&-PANEL_ID=p_dt_geo_map&-_lang=en&-geo_id=15000US150090303029&-CONTEXT=dt&-format=&-search_results=14000US15009030302&-ds_name=DEC_2000_SF1_U Block Group 9, Census Tract 303.02, Maui County]{{Dead link|date=2020年6月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}  United States Census Bureau</ref>。

